}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "genomic RNA", "obj": "RNA", "prob": 0.7034858465194702, "span": {"begin": 386, "end": 397}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:9576"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "accessory open reading frame (ORF) proteins", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.7938729524612427, "span": {"begin": 600, "end": 643}}, {"id": ["mesh:D045169"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "SARS-CoV", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.8826116919517517, "span": {"begin": 691, "end": 699}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SARS-CoV-2 virus", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.7766211032867432, "span": {"begin": 691, "end": 707}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "interferon I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9961338043212891, "span": {"begin": 747, "end": 759}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IFN-I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9981012344360352, "span": {"begin": 761, "end": 766}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "KE1901", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.6988323330879211, "span": {"begin": 787, "end": 793}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IFN-I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9855384826660156, "span": {"begin": 836, "end": 841}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IFN-I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9983288645744324, "span": {"begin": 889, "end": 894}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:340061"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "interferon-stimulated gene (ISG) proteins", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8546211123466492, "span": {"begin": 943, "end": 984}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SARS-CoV-2", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.8644140362739563, "span": {"begin": 1015, "end": 1025}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IFN-I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9972598552703857, "span": {"begin": 1044, "end": 1049}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3438"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "IFN-I", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9950894713401794, "span": {"begin": 1095, "end": 1100}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:340061"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "ISG proteins", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9745888710021973, "span": {"begin": 1105, "end": 1117}}], "text": "Upon entry of a virus into the host cell (KE1738), the virus is unpackaged from the structural nucleocapsid (N), envelope (E), and membrane (M) proteins.&nbsp;The viral RNA is detected by Pattern Recognition Receptor (PRR) proteins including RIG-I and MDA5 but the M proteins can interact with these PRRs directly, and block this initial host reaction (Fu et al., 2021).&nbsp;The viral genomic RNA can then be translated directly at the host ribosomes. The viral proteins are processed through&nbsp;cleavage by viral protease enzymes. This releases a repertoire of non-structural proteins (NSPs) and accessory open reading frame (ORF) proteins&nbsp;that has evolved, for example in&nbsp;the SARS-CoV-2 virus, to bind and block the proteins in the interferon I (IFN-I) antiviral cascade (KE1901). The normal function of the host&rsquo;s IFN-I response to other viruses is the expression of IFN-I which in turn stimulates the expression of many interferon-stimulated gene (ISG) proteins with antiviral functions. The SARS-CoV-2 antagonism of the IFN-I pathway delays or curtails the expression of IFN-I and ISG proteins.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:25:08 +0000 2026"}